South Africa has recorded 11 046 new COVID-19 cases on Thursday, bringing the cumulative number to 482 169 confirmed cases. 315 new COVID-19 related deaths have been reported in the last 24 hours with 121 from Eastern Cape, 96 from Gauteng, 55 from KwaZulu-Natal, 34 from Western Cape and 9 from North West. This brings the cumulative number of deaths to 7 812. The total number of tests conducted to date is 2 918 049 with 44 886 new tests conducted since the last report. The number of recoveries currently stands at 309 601 which translates to a recovery rate of 64%. #COVID19 Statistics in SA as at 30 July. pic.twitter.com/eosUEVBtgK — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) July 30, 2020  As of today,the total number of confirmed #COVID19 cases is 482 169, the total number of deaths is 7 812 and the total number of recoveries is 309 601. pic.twitter.com/kxNPcVCUdH — Dr Zweli Mkhize (@DrZweliMkhize) July 30, 2020 